    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "# Subplot 1\n",
        "x1 = [1, 2, 3]\n",
        "y1 = [4, 5, 5]\n",
        "plt.subplot(2, 3, 1)\n",
        "plt.plot(x1, y1)\n",
        "plt.title(\"Line Plot\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"X-axis\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Y-axis\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Subplot 2\n",
        "x2 = [100, 200, 300, 400]\n",
        "mylabels = [\"Cars\", \"Sports Bike\", \"Hyper Naked Bikes\", \"Scooters\"]\n",
        "mycolors = [\"blue\", \"red\", \"brown\", \"pink\"]\n",
        "myexplode = [0.1, 0.1, 0.1, 0.1]\n",
        "plt.subplot(2, 3, 2)\n",
        "plt.pie(x2, labels=mylabels, colors=mycolors, explode=myexplode, shadow=9)\n",
        "plt.title(\"Pie Chart\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Subplot 3\n",
        "x3 = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n",
        "y3 = [2, 4, 5, 8, 10]\n",
        "colors3 = [\"red\", \"green\", \"blue\", \"yellow\", \"purple\"]\n",
        "plt.subplot(2, 3, 3)\n",
        "plt.barh(x3, y3, color=colors3)\n",
        "plt.title(\"Horizontal Bar Graph\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"X-axis\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Y-axis\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Subplot 4\n",
        "plt.subplot(2, 3, 4)\n",
        "plt.bar(x3, y3, color=colors3)\n",
        "plt.title(\"Vertical Bar Graph\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"X-axis\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Y-axis\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Subplot 5\n",
        "plt.subplot(2, 3, 5)\n",
        "plt.scatter(x3, y3, s=[1000, 2000, 300, 4000, 500], c=['red', 'green', 'blue', 'yellow', 'purple'], marker=\"*\", edgecolors=\"black\", alpha=1)\n",
        "plt.title(\"Scatter Plot\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"X-axis\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Y-axis\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Adjust layout to prevent overlapping\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Show the subplots\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ],
